  // Social: "About 70 million Americans get Social Security — and millions are still calling the 800 number and sitting on hold for an hour when they could do the same thing online in 3 minutes. Your my Social Security account lets you check your earnings, estimate your benefits, apply for retirement, change direct deposit, and get a benefit letter — without ever picking up a phone. Here's exactly how to set it up."
  // Newsletter: "There is a free, government-run website at ssa.gov that lets you do almost anything with your Social Security — check your earnings record, estimate what you'll collect at retirement, apply for benefits, switch your direct deposit, print a benefit letter for your mortgage lender, even request a replacement Social Security card. No phone calls. No 40-minute holds. No trips to a crowded field office. This guide walks through exactly how to set up your my Social Security account, use Login.gov or ID.me to sign in securely, and use every feature that matters. And critically — how to spot the scams. The real SSA will NEVER call you threatening arrest. If you get that call, hang up."
